529507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 26, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lcw1665702604012.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lcw1665702604012.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lcw1665702604012.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lcw1665702604012\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      ProcScript for Data Validation\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">ProcScript instructions can be used to explicitly validate data, set validation conditions, check modification and validation status, and handle errors.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__section_w4468ab1b5b1_w4469ab1b5_w4470ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__section_w4471ab1b5b3_w4472ab1b5_w4473ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d708569e56\">\n                        \n ProcScript Statements for Data Validation\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__p_d45152e1_d45153e1_d45154e1\">You can start validation for various object levels by the following ProcScript statements.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">ProcScript Statements for Data Validation</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__1\">\n ProcScript Statement\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__2\">\n Action\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__3\">\n Scope\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lrk1665702576500.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lrk1665702576500.html\" title=\"Determines whether the valerr data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. This attribute holds the occurrence or field validation error (depending on whether the selected item is an entity or field). Valid values are True or False (default).\">Validate</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__2\">\n Validate all data marked as modified.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__3\">\n Component entities\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validate/e</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__2\">\n Validate modified occurrences of an entity, and its inner entities\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__3\">\n Entity\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validate/o</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__2\">\n Validate the current occurrence of an entity and its inner entities\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__3\">\n Occurrence, including inner entities\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bwv1665702576896.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bwv1665702576896.html\" title=\"Validate an occurrence.\">validateocc</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__2\">\n Validate an occurrence\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__3\">\n Occurrence, excluding inner entities\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fdp1665702576817.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fdp1665702576817.html\" title=\"Validate a key of the current occurrence.\">validatekey</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__2\">\n Validate a key of the current occurrence.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__3\">\n Key\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jwi1665702576586.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jwi1665702576586.html\" title=\"Validate a field of the current occurrence.\">validatefield</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__2\">\n Validate a field of the current occurrence.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lcw1665702604012__table_d4364e1_d4365e1_d4366e1__entry__3\">\n Field\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__section_w4474ab1b5b5_w4475ab1b5_w4476ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d708569e214\">\n                        \n Validation Status Functions\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__p_d45158e1_d45159e1_d45160e1\">Validation status functions enable you to check whether or not an object requires validation. They are set when data is modified and reset after the data has been validated; they cannot be set by ProcScript.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22388e1_d22389e1_d22390e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qdc1665702602510.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdc1665702602510.html\" title=\"Identify whether a field requires validation.\">$fieldvalidation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22391e1_d22392e1_d22393e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wcw1719485700746.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wcw1719485700746.html\" title=\"Identify whether a primary or candidate key requires validation.\">$keyvalidation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22394e1_d22395e1_d22396e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fpz1719812992669.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fpz1719812992669.html\" title=\"Check whether an occurrence requires validation.\">$occvalidation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22397e1_d22398e1_d22399e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"biz1719502191613.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/biz1719502191613.html\" title=\"Identify whether data in the component instance requires validation.\">$instancevalidation</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__p_d45161e1_d45162e1_d45163e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wfh1665702604181.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wfh1665702604181.html\" title=\"All fields, keys, and occurrences have validation and modification flags which are used to determine data should be validated or stored. In general, when the content of a field is changed, the associated validation and modification flags are set to TRUE.\">Validation and Modification Flags</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__section_w4477ab1b5b7_w4478ab1b5_w4479ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d708569e279\">\n                        \n Modification Status Functions\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__p_d45167e1_d45168e1_d45169e1\">Modification functions enable you to check the modification status of an object. Validating an object does not reset any of these modification functions. The modification status is reset only on the completion of a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span> process.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22400e1_d22401e1_d22402e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rjy1665702601052.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rjy1665702601052.html\" title=\"Return the modification status of a field.\">$fieldmod</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22403e1_d22404e1_d22405e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aul1665702602685.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aul1665702602685.html\" title=\"Return the modification status of a database field.\">$fielddbmod</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22406e1_d22407e1_d22408e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nij1665702601782.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nij1665702601782.html\" title=\"Return a value indicating whether the specified key has been modified.\">$keymod</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22409e1_d22410e1_d22411e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eai1665702600334.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eai1665702600334.html\" title=\"Return the modification status of an occurrence.\">$occmod</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22412e1_d22413e1_d22414e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uli1665702604314.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uli1665702604314.html\" title=\"Return the modification status of a database occurrence.\">$occdbmod</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22415e1_d22416e1_d22417e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uni1718715029734.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uni1718715029734.html\" title=\"Return the modification status of data in the current Form component.\">$formmod (deprecated)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22418e1_d22419e1_d22420e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"arl1665702601386.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/arl1665702601386.html\" title=\"Return the modification status of database fields in the current Form.\">$formdbmod (deprecated)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22421e1_d22422e1_d22423e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"atw1665702600492.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/atw1665702600492.html\" title=\"Return or set the modification status of data in the current component instance.\">$instancemod</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22424e1_d22425e1_d22426e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"len1665702601301.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/len1665702601301.html\" title=\"Return the modification status of database fields in the current component instance.\">$instancedbmod</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__section_w4480ab1b5b9_w4481ab1b5_w4482ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d708569e385\">\n                        \n Validation Request Functions\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__p_d45173e1_d45174e1_d45175e1\">There are situations where data can be new (not stored in the database) but validation flags are not set on. This often occurs when initial values are declared for a field in its <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Initial Value</span> property, or assigned in ProcScript using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/init</span> (for example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">FLD1/init=<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n</code>). Initial values are not taken into consideration for validation because they are not regarded as real data. To validate an initial value, you must explicitly request data validation for the field.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__p_d45176e1_d45177e1_d45178e1\">The following ProcScript functions can be set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">TRUE</code> to force the validation of an object, regardless of the modification or validation status.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22427e1_d22428e1_d22429e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"swr1665702599962.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/swr1665702599962.html\" title=\"Return or set the requirement for field validation.\">$fieldcheck</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22430e1_d22431e1_d22432e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"flp1665702599747.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/flp1665702599747.html\" title=\"Indicate whether a specified primary or candidate key should be validated.\">$keycheck</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22433e1_d22434e1_d22435e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hnz1719661363571.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hnz1719661363571.html\" title=\"Return or set the requirement for checking an occurrence.\">$occcheck</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__p_d45179e1_d45180e1_d45181e1\">Setting these functions ensures that the validation triggers fire at the next opportunity (for example, when a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span> statement is issued). Alternatively, you can use ProcScript statements to activate the validation triggers immediately.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__p_d45182e1_d45183e1_d45184e1\">Note that <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occheck</span> implicitly also causes fields and keys of an occurrence to be checked and the occurrence's validate trigger fired. Similarly, when a key is validated, the fields comprising the key are also validated.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__section_w4483ab1b5c11_w4484ab1b5_w4485ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d708569e459\">\n                        \n Key Handling Functions\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__p_d45188e1_d45189e1_d45190e1\">The following ProcScript functions obtain information about keys, including primary keys, candidate keys and index fields.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22436e1_d22437e1_d22438e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sse1719818928383.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sse1719818928383.html\" title=\"Return the number of the current key in a validateKey or leaveModifiedKey trigger.\">$curkey</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22439e1_d22440e1_d22441e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"epv1719810593542.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/epv1719810593542.html\" title=\"Return the total number of keys for an entity.\">$totkeys</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22442e1_d22443e1_d22444e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dmp1665702603557.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dmp1665702603557.html\" title=\"Return a list of the fields that make up a primary or candidate key or index.\">$keyfields</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcw1665702604012__li_d22445e1_d22446e1_d22447e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"upd1665702601935.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/upd1665702601935.html\" title=\"Return the type of the specified key.\">$keytype</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wfh1665702604181.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Validation and Modification Flags</a><p>All fields, keys, and occurrences have validation and modification flags which are used to determine data should be validated or stored. In general, when the content of a field is changed, the associated validation and modification flags are set to TRUE.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ProcScript for Data Validation Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 ProcScript for Data Validation ProcScript instructions can be used to explicitly validate data, set validation conditions, check modification and validation status, and handle errors. ProcScript Statements for Data Validation You can start validation for various object levels by the following ProcScript statements. Table 1. ProcScript Statements for Data Validation ProcScript Statement Action Scope Validate Validate all data marked as modified. Component entities validate/e Validate modified occurrences of an entity, and its inner entities Entity validate/o Validate the current occurrence of an entity and its inner entities Occurrence, including inner entities validateocc Validate an occurrence Occurrence, excluding inner entities validatekey Validate a key of the current occurrence. Key validatefield Validate a field of the current occurrence. Field Validation Status Functions Validation status functions enable you to check whether or not an object requires validation. They are set when data is modified and reset after the data has been validated; they cannot be set by ProcScript. $fieldvalidation $keyvalidation $occvalidation $instancevalidation For more information, see Validation and Modification Flags . Modification Status Functions Modification functions enable you to check the modification status of an object. Validating an object does not reset any of these modification functions. The modification status is reset only on the completion of a store process. $fieldmod $fielddbmod $keymod $occmod $occdbmod $formmod (deprecated) $formdbmod (deprecated) $instancemod $instancedbmod Validation Request Functions There are situations where data can be new (not stored in the database) but validation flags are not set on. This often occurs when initial values are declared for a field in its Initial Value property, or assigned in ProcScript using /init (for example, FLD1/init= Value ). Initial values are not taken into consideration for validation because they are not regarded as real data. To validate an initial value, you must explicitly request data validation for the field. The following ProcScript functions can be set to TRUE to force the validation of an object, regardless of the modification or validation status. $fieldcheck $keycheck $occcheck Setting these functions ensures that the validation triggers fire at the next opportunity (for example, when a store statement is issued). Alternatively, you can use ProcScript statements to activate the validation triggers immediately. Note that $occheck implicitly also causes fields and keys of an occurrence to be checked and the occurrence's validate trigger fired. Similarly, when a key is validated, the fields comprising the key are also validated. Key Handling Functions The following ProcScript functions obtain information about keys, including primary keys, candidate keys and index fields. $curkey $totkeys $keyfields $keytype Related Links Validation and Modification Flags All fields, keys, and occurrences have validation and modification flags which are used to determine data should be validated or stored. In general, when the content of a field is changed, the associated validation and modification flags are set to TRUE. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}